message: #13006 Whoever those girls were at PBE on Saturday in green body suits dancing on the table next to the DJ were the definition of life of the party. Unsure who they are but they should be at every MIT party from now on.

#13004 I feel like after graduating, people just kind of slowly disappear. A lot of my friends have graduated and are doing real world stuff. I know it's bound to happen because that's just how life works, but it's sad to see everyone scatter across different locations. Communication falls off and there aren't a lot of common things to talk about anymore because you don't see them all the time on campus. I just wish there was an easy way to initiate conversations without them seeming so sudden or out of place.
#12998 One of my fraternity brothers/roommates and his girlfriend talk to each other in these weird, like, baby voices? it annoys the shit out of me tbh. probably more than it should.
